ting Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/bootcamps/ai/handson/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Preparation</title> <description>&lt;h2&gt;1. &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.lxp.lu/first-steps/quick_start/&#34;&gt;How to login to MeluXina machine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;[Please take a look if you are using Windows](https://docs.lxp.l...&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/bootcamps/ai/preparation/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:01:10 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_created.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/bootcamps/ai/preparation/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Introduction</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Introduction to GPU programming using CUDA&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;figure markdown&gt; [![](figures/CUDA-July-2025-Front-Page.png)](https://github.com/NCCLUX/NCC-Trainings/blob/513...</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:01:10 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_created.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Hello world</title> <description>&lt;p&gt;Our first exercise would be to print out &#34;Hello World&#34; from the GPU. To do that, we need to do the following things:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Run a part or the entire application ...&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-1/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:01:10 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_created.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-1/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Vector addition</title> <description>&lt;p&gt;In this hands-on session, we will delve into the fundamentals of vector addition on the Graphics Processing Unit (GPU) utilizing the CUDA programming model. ...&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-2/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:01:10 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_created.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-2/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Matrix multiplication</title> <description>&lt;p&gt;We will now look into basic matrix multiplication. In this tutorial, we will explore the process of matrix multiplication, a fundamental operation in linear ...&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-3/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:01:10 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_created.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-3/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Shared memory</title> <description>&lt;p&gt;In this tutorial, we will explore the concept of shared memory matrix multiplication. This technique involves partitioning the global matrix into smaller til...&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-4/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:01:10 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_created.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-4/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Unified memory</title> <description>&lt;p&gt;Unified memory streamlines the data transfer process between the host (CPU) and the device (GPU), minimizing the need for explicit data movement by programme...&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-5/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:01:10 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_created.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/exercise-5/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Preparation</title> <description>&lt;h4&gt;1. &lt;a href=&#34;https://docs.lxp.lu/first-steps/quick_start/&#34;&gt;How to login to the MeluXina machine&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h4&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;1.1 [Please take a look if you are using Windows](https://docs...&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/preparation/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:01:10 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_created.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/preparation/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Profiling and performance</title> <description>&lt;h3&gt;Time measurement&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;In CUDA, the execution time can be measured by using the CUDA events. CUDA API events shall be created using &lt;code&gt;cudaEvent_t&lt;/code&gt;, for example...&lt;/p&gt;</description> <link>https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/profiling/</link> <pubDate>Mon, 27 Apr 2026 18:01:10 +0000</pubDate> <source url="https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/feed_rss_created.xml">SuperComputing Luxembourg - National Competence Center</source><guid isPermaLink="true">https://ncclux.github.io/NCC-Trainings/courses/cuda/profiling/</guid> </item> <item> <title>Introduction</title> <description>&lt;h1&gt;Electronic structure methods used in industry from ph